    "They can be solved reliably and efficiently, even when they involve a very large number of variables and constraints, and involve nonlinear, even nondifferentiable, functions [BV04].",
    "Shortly before Markowitz published his paper on portfolio selection, George Dantzig developed the simplex method [Dan51], which allowed for the efficient solution of linear programs.",
